properties.Name: LienType
properties.Description:
A classification of types of Liens.

Ex:
ARTISANS LIEN
Artisan liens are imposed on personal property other than real estate or things attached to real estate.  Artisans liens are imposed because of nonpayment for materials or services that benefit personal property.
 
INCOME TAX LIEN
Income tax liens are imposed by state and federal government when personal or business income taxes are unpaid.
 
JUDGMENT LIEN
A judgment lien comes into effect after a party has won a lawsuit.  If the party that loses the lawsuit is unable to pay, the winning party may get a judgment lien, which can be attached to the loser's property.
 
MECHANICS LIEN
A mechanics lien can be imposed on property that has benefited by the materials or services improvements that have not been paid.

The lien attaches when the materials and supplies are delivered, not when the lien is actually filed.
 
PROPERTY TAX LIEN
Property tax liens are imposed by government taxing authorities.
